      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(scripts): timeout crabbox wrapper sanity checks",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a bounded timeout (`5_000ms`) to crabbox wrapper sanity probes (`--version`, `run --help`)\n- enforce `SIGKILL` on timeout and return a deterministic timeout status for stale/hung binaries\n- keep the PR scoped to `scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs`; the release/postpublish verifier changes were removed from this branch\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** A stale or hung Crabbox binary can block `scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs` forever during the `--version` or `run --help` sanity probes. After this patch, each sanity probe has a 5-second timeout and the wrapper exits deterministically when the selected binary hangs.\n- **Real environment tested:** Windows 11 local OpenClaw checkout using Node.js from the normal workstation PATH. I placed a fake `crabbox.exe` first on PATH; that executable sleeps for 60 seconds to simulate a hung Crabbox binary.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** `PATH=<fakebin>;$PATH; node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs -- --version`\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the patched branch:\n\n```text\n[crabbox] bin=crabbox version=unknown providers=unknown\n[crabbox] selected binary failed basic --version/--help sanity checks\n\nExitCode ElapsedSeconds\n-------- --------------\n       2          10.11\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The wrapper did not hang on the 60-second fake Crabbox binary. It killed the hung sanity probes and exited with code `2` after about `10.11s`, matching two bounded 5-second probes.\n- **What was not tested:** I did not run a live Crabbox hydration job; this proof isolates the wrapper sanity-probe hang path that this PR changes.\n\n## Verification\n- `node --check scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs`\n- `oxfmt --check --threads=1 scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs`\n- hung-binary wrapper proof above",
